Project Dependencies:

Node.js

    To install node.js on Mac, run:
    $ brew install node

    To instal Nodejs on Linux, run:
    $ curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_6.x | sudo -E bash -
    $ sudo apt-get install -y nodejs

npm

    To install npm on Linux, run:
    $ sudo apt-get install -y npm

nginx

    To install nginx on Linux, run:
    $ sudo apt-get install -y nginx

MongoDB

    Go to https://www.mongodb.com/download-center?filter=enterprise&gclid=Cj0KEQiA08rBBRDUn4qproqwzYMBEiQAqpzns7UbS_M0a_zlxwHy3xECl9WveImnved6GC9cgtA7MgUaAkAm8P8HAQ#enterprise
    to download the MongDB database application
    
    in Terminal, navigate to it's bin folder and run 
    mongod --dbpath ~/mapping-justice/userdata/ --port 27017 --smallfiles
    to establish connection on port 27017 (localhost)
    
    

===============================================================================

Configuring the environment:

Pull the required Javascripts:
$ npm install

Configure nginx (CURRENTLY LINUX ONLY, open the file to see what it does)
$ sudo ./config/webserver.sh

===============================================================================

Operating the application:

To start the site, run the following from the project root directory:
$ npm start

To view the map, visit the following URL:
localhost

